## State management — Zustand

```ts
// src/modules/<domain>/hooks/use<Domain>Store.ts
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface MyState {
  items: MyResource[];
  isLoading: boolean;
  setItems: (items: MyResource[]) => void;
  setLoading: (loading: boolean) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}

const initialState = { items: [], isLoading: false };

export const useMyStore = create<MyState>()((set) => ({
  ...initialState,
  setItems: (items) => set({ items }),
  setLoading: (isLoading) => set({ isLoading }),
  reset: () => set(initialState),
}));
```

- Always export with `use` prefix
- Always include `reset()` action
- Use `persist` only for state that must survive page refresh (auth, preferences)

---

## Authentication

Token is managed by `useAuthStore` (persisted to localStorage).
`apiFetch` injects the `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header automatically — never pass the token manually.

Protected routes:
```tsx
<Route element={<ProtectedRoute />}>
  <Route path="/dashboard" element={<DashboardPage />} />
</Route>
```

---

## Page pattern

Pages compose components and orchestrate hooks. They do not make API calls directly:

```tsx
export const MyPage: React.FC = () => {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useMyData();
  if (isLoading) return <LoadingSpinner />;
  if (error) return <ErrorMessage message={error} />;
  return (
    <AppLayout>
      <MyComponentA data={data} />
    </AppLayout>
  );
};
```

